ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Do you tend to become vigilant and wary of your surroundings?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you feel awkward when you are approached by someone new?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to become quiet?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to approach people whom you don't know and talk to them?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to spend time observing strangers from a distance first, before being able to mix in?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to be chatty in conversation when you are speaking to someone new?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Are you likely to spend most of your time next to a person whom you know well?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to feel physically anxious (e.g. racing pulse, sweaty, butterflies)?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to introduce yourself to new people?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to keep a fair distance away from strangers?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you tend to withdraw and retreat from those around you?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you prefer your own company over the company of others?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you usually enjoy going to social events with large crowds of people?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Would you tend to choose solitary leisure activities over spending time with close friends?
Notes: 0 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 2 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: Do you prefer to be surrounded by lively activity rather than a quiet gathering?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time

ElementDescription: If physically able, would you enjoy adventure holidays with some element of risk?
Notes: 2 = no/hardly ever; 1 = some of the time; 0 = yes/most of the time
